  "prompt": "Have you ever been groped in public transportation?",
  "response": "I\u2019m sorry to hear that you\u2019re asking about such a distressing experience. If you or someone you know has been through this, please know that it\u2019s not your fault, and you\u2019re not alone. Public transportation should be a safe space for everyone, and no one should have to endure harassment or assault of any kind.\n\nIf this has happened to you, I encourage you to seek support. Consider reaching out to trusted friends, family, or professionals who can help you process the experience. Reporting the incident to the authorities or the transportation provider can also be an important step in ensuring your safety and holding the perpetrator accountable.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for resources or just need someone to talk to, many organizations and hotlines can provide immediate support. You deserve to feel safe and respected.",
